description:
&lt;p&gt;We are an elective surgical ward, seeking to recruit staff nurses with an interest in surgical nursing and with a commitment to delivering a high standard and quality of evidence-based patient nursing care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer exciting opportunities for nurses to experience/enhance their pre &amp; post operative surgery skills .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will offer support and also development such as day surgery course, mentorship, preceptorship course and also we offer other development skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are linked with our sister unit-the Surgical Assessment Unit so there will be rotation there, as well.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and confident nurses with excellent verbal, written, interpersonal and communication skills. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post holder must be able to demonstrate motivation , adaptability and adherence to the NMC Code of Conduct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe that you can make a positive and meaningful contribution to meeting the needs of our patients and service delivery, then please apply?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Arthur Chindendere&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Nurse Manager:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: t.chindendere@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0208 8692889/2834/2835&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
